$ on the line. Among applications of this result, we show that for a large\nclass of locally moving groups, the standard action is locally rigid, in the\nsense that every sufficiently small perturbation in the compact-open topology\ngives a semi-conjugate action. This is based on an analysis of the space of\nharmonic actions on the line for such groups.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Apr 2021 22:12:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-03"}
