 transition is fully reversible and the bubble can be thawed back\ninto a droplet if the magnetic field is increased under current. Whereas the\ndroplet collapses without a sustaining current, the bubble is highly stable and\nremains intact for days without external drive. Electrical measurements are\ncomplemented by direct observation using scanning transmission x-ray\nmicroscopy, which corroborates the analysis and confirms that the bubble is\nstabilized by pinning.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Apr 2021 10:45:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-01"}
